To remove an item from the front of the list, use the Perl-style method Shift

    Dim objArray As New clsArray
    objArray.Delimeter = ":"
    Dim strMyStuff As String
    strMyStuff = "Pears:Apples:Grapes:Bananas:Kiwis"
    objArray.SetArrayFromString content:=strMyStuff
    
    ... bunch of nifty code ...
    
Now process one item from the front of the list
    Dim strItem as String
    strItem = objArray.Shift
    ... do stuff with strItem ...

Now process all the items in the list from the front end AND remove the item
from the list, thus shortening the list with each pass.
METHOD No. 1
    Dim strItem as String
    Do While objArray.CountRemaining > 0
        strItem = objArray.Shift
        ... do stuff with strItem ...
    Loop
